The paper focuses on human-AI interaction and uses a brain-computer-interface to detect an individual's level of interest in objects/events in a virtual environment. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper uses Deep Reinforcement Learning AI agents, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques to detect objects in the virtual environment. Furthermore, the paper discusses how the AI agent learns and adapts its behavior, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Finally, the paper involves neural signatures, which suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
